==English==

===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[goma]]'', from Germanic.  Cognate with German ''[[Gaumen]]'' ‘palate’, Old Norse ''[[gomr]]'' ‘palate’.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌm|-ʌm]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# The [[flesh]] round the [[teeth]].

